abstract = {This paper discusses the emerging paradigm of the Internet of Things (IoT), focusing on the important role that people will play in the future connected world of digitized services and electronic "Things". The associated research highlights how IoT is influencing changes and requirements in communication required to facilitate decision making between systems, devices and people in a connected world. The paper provides background context on the development of IoT technologies and how these developments overlap with industry, enabling revolutionary changes such as Industry 4.0 and the advent of the Industrial Internet. The emergence of IoT technologies, IoT enabled industry and IoT influenced social change are discussed, highlighting the new requirements and production demands that are emerging for integrated communications, features and systems.The paper introduces a new end-to-end and framework for enterprise planning, adoption and deployment of a feature rich and integrated Unified Communications and Collaboration (UC&amp;C) system within a multinational enterprise. The new framework presents a multi-domain structure with four primary modular containers. This structured model introduces new concepts of a Core Governance Domain (CGD), Operational Management Domain (OMD), Unified Services Domain (USD) and Integrated Feature Domain (IFD). Combined these domains represent a coherent framework that supports initial deployment and planning, ongoing sustain and technical agile technical architecture. This research has been carried out within the scope of a multi-year automotive focused study in General Motors.},
